      <div class="site-section pb-0">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row align-items-stretch">
            <div class="col-md-8" data-aos="fade-up">
              <img src="assets/img/img_1.jpg" alt="Image" class="img-fluid">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 ml-auto" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
              <div class="sticky-content">
                <h3 class="h3"></h3>
                <p class="mb-4"><span class="text-muted">Food</span></p>

                <div class="mb-5">
                  <p>Pilaf - South Indian Pilaf </p>
                </div>

                <h4 class="h4 mb-3">Preparation for Pilaf</h4>
                <ul class="list-unstyled list-line mb-5">
                  <li>Oil</li>
                  <li>2 Tomatoes</li>
                  <li>5 Onions</li>
                  <li>2 spoons of Chilli Powder</li>
                  <li>2 Spoons of Coriander Powder</li>
                  <li>2 Spoons of Garam Masala Powder</li>
                  <li>Bay Leaf</li>
                  <li>Cardommom Seeds</li>
                  <li>Cinnamon Seeds</li>
                  <li>Cumin Seeds</li>
                  <li>Red Chillies Dry</li>
                  <li>Chicken</li>
                  <li>Ginger Garlic Paste</li>
                  <li>Mint leaves</li>
                  <li>Corriander Leaves</li>
                  <li>Yogurt</li>
                  <li>Salt</li>


                <h4 class="h4 mb-3">Direction to Rasam</h4>
                <ul class="list-unstyled list-line mb-5">
                  <li>Add 4-5 spoons of oil and ghee. Add chopped onions and fry until its golden brown.</li>
                  <li>Add ginger garlic paste, Chicken pieces Fry for a bit.</li>
                  <li>Add sliced Tomaotes, Chilli powder, coriander powder, Garam masala Powder, coriander leaves, mint leaves, 1-2 spoons of yogurt and cook for 5-8 mins on medium flame.</li>
                  <li>Add water depending on the amount of rice required.</li>
                  <li>Add Salt to taste</li>
                  <li>Add water depending on the amount of rice required.</li>
                  <li>Let it simmer until the rice is done.</li>

                  Enjoy!
                </ul>

